nl.naturalis.lims2.oaipmh

Class AnnotatedDocumentComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.naturalis.lims2.oaipmh.AnnotatedDocumentComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<AnnotatedDocument>

    public class AnnotatedDocumentComparator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<AnnotatedDocument>
    Compares AnnotatedDocument instances based on whether one references the other, or whether one is input for the other. If one AnnotatedDocument references another AnnotatedDocument, it means it has superseded the other AnnotatedDocument. Thus when sorting AnnotatedDocument instances, those that reference others should be pushed up, while those that are referenced should be pushed down.
    Author:
    Ayco Holleman

        public int compare(AnnotatedDocument ad0,

        Compares the specified AnnotatedDocument instances. A side-effect of the comparison is that the referenced document will be marked as dispensable. That is, it will be excluded from the OAI-PMH output.
